# The API image is `dotnet publish API` — it needs only the .NET projects + API/wwwroot
# (the widget is already pre-built into API/wwwroot/pointer.js). Everything below is either a
# separate deliverable (extension, widget source, generated clients), bind-mounted at runtime
# (landing), or build cruft — excluding it keeps the Docker build context small and deploys fast.

# Node / frontend deliverables (not part of the API image)
node_modules
**/node_modules
extension
web-component
clients
landing
dist
**/dist

# .NET build output (restored fresh inside the build stage)
**/bin
**/obj

# Repo cruft
.git
.github
.vs
.vscode
docs
scripts
Tests
.env*
*.log

# NOTE: do NOT add `**/*.md` — API/wwwroot/skill.md is served by the API and must stay in the image.
